Exercise a failing remap epilog: the NGC body runs, then the epilog fails and must
abort the remap, convey the error text, and leave the interpreter usable.

Re-expressed for gomc: the classic test used a Python epilog that returned
INTERP_ERROR.  gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter, so M400's epilog is a
C interp_ext handler (cmod test_remap_fail, failingepilog) that calls set_error()
and returns INTERP_EXT_ERROR.  The driver runs M400 via MDI; checkresult confirms
the NGC body (mustbecalled -> o<mark_body>) DID run, the epilog then failed, its
error text was conveyed, and a follow-up MDI still works.
